FT  07 SEP 92 / Construction Contracts: Edinburgh conference centre
GA MANAGEMENT, part of the Scottish-based GA Holdings, has been awarded a
Pounds 33m contract by the Edinburgh International Conference Centre (EICC)
to manage the design and construction of the city's international conference
centre.
EICC, which is a joint venture between Edinburgh District Council, Lothian
and Edinburgh Enterprise and Lothian Regional Council, has commissioned a
1,200-seat showcase conference centre situated between Lothian Road and
Morrison Street. It will be linked to a new Pounds 250m international
financial centre.
Clearance and land engineering work on the site is well advanced and work
has also started on the realignment of the Western Approach Road in
preparation for further development of the 10-acre site.
